        "content": "<p>I'm aware of theorems spelling it as \"nonzero\", \"nonZero\", \"non_zero\", \"neZero\", and \"ne_zero\". The second option is mostly confined to the <code>NeZero</code> structure, but not entirely, e.g. <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Equiv/Basic.html#LinearEquiv.smulOfNeZero\">LinearEquiv.smulOfNeZero</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/GroupWithZero/Units/Equiv.html#unitsEquivNeZero\">unitsEquivNeZero</a></p>\n<p>examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=mul_ne_zero_iff#doc\">docs#mul_ne_zero_iff</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=div_ne_zero_iff#doc\">docs#div_ne_zero_iff</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=pos_of_ne_zero#doc\">docs#pos_of_ne_zero</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/Localization/FractionRing.html#IsFractionRing.to_map_ne_zero_of_mem_nonZeroDivisors\">IsFractionRing.to_map_ne_zero_of_mem_nonZeroDivisors</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Degree/Support.html#Polynomial.natDegree_mem_support_of_nonzero\">Polynomial.natDegree_mem_support_of_nonzero</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/GoingUp.html#Ideal.exists_nonzero_mem_of_ne_bot\">Ideal.exists_nonzero_mem_of_ne_bot</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/GroupTheory/GroupAction/SubMulAction.html#Units.orbitRel_nonZero_iff\">Units.orbitRel_nonZero_iff</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/EquivReindex.html#NumberField.det_of_basisMatrix_non_zero\">NumberField.det_of_basisMatrix_non_zero</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Analysis/Matrix/Spectrum.html#Matrix.IsHermitian.rank_eq_card_non_zero_eigs\">Matrix.IsHermitian.rank_eq_card_non_zero_eigs</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>I also found <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/Discriminant.html#Algebra.discr_not_zero_of_basis\">Algebra.discr_not_zero_of_basis</a> but I think that one is just objectively a wrong name. :)</p>\n<p>The <code>pos</code>/<code>neg</code>/<code>nonneg</code>/<code>nonpos</code> convention fixes this for other relations, but maybe it would be good to fix this for nonequality?</p>",
        "id": 574563906,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Meiburg",
        "timestamp": 1771435218
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just use <code>ne_zero</code> please (except for uses of <code>NeZero</code> which should become <code>neZero</code> by the convention)</p>",
        "id": 574564200,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1771435302
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/leanprover-community.github.io/pull/789\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/leanprover-community.github.io/pull/789</a>, then?</p>",
        "id": 574565995,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Meiburg",
        "timestamp": 1771435811
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(And <code>fooNeZero</code> / <code>neZeroFoo</code> are correct for <code>def</code>s)</p>",
